# STM32 Code Generation Rules

## LL Library Only
- Generated STM32 code MUST use LL (Low-Layer) library functions (`LL_GPIO_*`, `LL_RCC_*`, etc.)
- HAL library calls (`HAL_*`) are FORBIDDEN unless the user explicitly requests HAL
- If HAL calls are detected in generated output, flag them and regenerate

## Safety Checks Required
- All generated C code MUST pass `check_code_safety()` before being written to disk
- All generated C code MUST pass `validate_generated_code()` for structural quality
- These checks live in `stloop/code_validator.py` and must be called in the `gen()` flow before file write

## System Prompt Requirements
When modifying the system prompt for code generation, it MUST include:
1. Explicit LL library constraint with example includes
2. `SystemClock_Config()` with HSE-to-HSI fallback error handling
3. Register address comments for non-obvious peripheral configuration
4. At least one few-shot example (blink pattern recommended)

## Dangerous Patterns
Never allow generated code containing:
- `system()`, `exec*()`, `popen()` calls
- Inline assembly (`__asm`, `asm(`) without explicit user request
- `#include <stdlib.h>` or `#include <unistd.h>` (not needed for bare-metal)
